    "The distribution of dataset sources in the primary studies is shown in Fig. 7.",
    "Based on our analysis, 54 % of primary studies used collected datasets to detect smart contract vulnerabilities as shown in Table 8.",
    "It is believed that this trend is because smart contract analysis is a relatively new field of research and there are not widely used, standardized benchmarks for tasks such as vulnerability detection.",
    "Researchers thus must collect data from multiple resources to capture a wide range of vulnerabilities, code structures, and coding practices present in the actual smart contracts used in various applications.",
    "Researchers rely on benchmark datasets to assess and compare the efficacy of various ML models."
